unittitle_ssm: Village of Jamaica, Queens County temperance collection
abstract_ssm: This collection consists of 1833 meeting minutes and constitution of the Temperance Society of School District No. 4 in the Village of Jamaica, Queens County and an 1855 petition to the village's Board of Trustees requesting an increase in the number of police officers to combat the problems of "intemperance and profanity."
